"GNOW": "Gnawed. Chaucer.",
"GNU": "One of two species of large South African antelopes of thegenus Catoblephas, having a mane and bushy tail, and curved horns inboth sexes. [Written also gnoo.]",
"GO": "Gone. Chaucer.",
"GO-BETWEEN": "An intermediate agent; a broker; a procurer; -- usually in adisparaging sense. Shak.",
"GO-BY": "A passing without notice; intentional neglect; thrusting away;a shifting off; adieu; as, to give a proposal the go-by.Some songs to which we have given the go-by. Prof. Wilson.",
